							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Coviello-author-pic-150x150.jpeg" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Coviello-author-pic-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Peter Coviello" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Peter Coviello</h4>
												<p>Peter Coviello is the author of six books, including <i>Long Players</i>, a memoir selected as one of <i>ARTFORUM</i>’s Best Books of 2018; <i>Make Yourselves Gods</i>, about the Mormon nineteenth century; and most recently <i>Is There God After Prince?: Dispatches from an Age of Last Things. </i>He<i> </i>taught for many years at Bowdoin College and since 2014 has been at UIC, where he is Professor and Head of English.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
